<subsection xml:id="subsec-Application_of_Linear_Equations_in_One_Unknown">
      <title>Application of Linear Equations in One Unknown</title>

        <example>

          <statement>

            <p>
              Dorine and Andrew are to share <m>10</m> kg of sugar so that Dorine gets <m>2</m> kg more than what Andrew receives. Find the weight received by each of them.
            </p>

          </statement>

          <solution>

            <p>
              Let Andrew's share be <m>x</m> kg.
            </p>

            <p>
              Dorine's share is; <me>= x + 2.</me>
            </p>

            <p>
              Thus, <me>x + x + 2 = 10.</me>
            </p>

            <p>
              <me>2x + 2 = 10.</me>
            </p>

            <p>
              <me>2x = 8.</me>
            </p>

            <p>
              <me>x = 4</me>
            </p>

            <p>
              Andrew's share is <m>4</m> kg and Dorine's share is <m>6</m> kg.
            </p>

          </solution>

        </example>

